I'll have to retreat for today!

257
00:13:03,502 --> 00:13:05,367
Hang on, you forgot your science thingy!

258
00:13:09,422 --> 00:13:10,199
So then,

259
00:13:10,914 --> 00:13:15,012
have you given any thought to what you might
want to do in the future at all, Miss Minakami?

260
00:13:15,382 --> 00:13:16,712
I have thought about it.

261
00:13:19,442 --> 00:13:23,024
Uh... So, are you planning on finding a job?

262
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:27,898
Then... are you... looking into higher education?

263
00:13:27,977 --> 00:13:33,299
Uh... 'Kay that means...

264
00:13:35,181 --> 00:13:38,150
I think I get it.

265
00:13:52,681 --> 00:13:54,176
Hey, you find it yet?

266
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:56,817
It's no good.

267
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,073
We can't find the cube.

268
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,552
I thought we stored that thing somewhere safe.

269
00:14:00,596 --> 00:14:02,199
How could it just disappear?

270
00:14:02,729 --> 00:14:04,169
Well, look on the bright side.

271
00:14:04,234 --> 00:14:07,363
There's gonna be a huge cash reward
for whoever finds the dang thing.

272
00:14:07,491 --> 00:14:09,858
I'd say that's worth all the trouble we're going through.

273
00:14:10,073 --> 00:14:11,012
Ha, yeah!

274
00:14:11,206 --> 00:14:13,238
If we can find one, then we can find the other.

275
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:14,204
Better keep looking.

276
00:14:14,778 --> 00:14:17,069
If I could just get my hands on that cube.

277
00:14:17,161 --> 00:14:19,361
I wonder if that would help me
get in the King's good graces.

278
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:21,147
Hey, uh, who's that?

279
00:14:21,388 --> 00:14:22,180
Over there?

280
00:14:22,317 --> 00:14:23,167
Huh?

281
00:14:28,381 --> 00:14:29,586
My wooden cube.

282
00:14:29,908 --> 00:14:30,726
Give it back.

283
00:14:36,424 --> 00:14:37,364
Hey, now.

284
00:14:37,389 --> 00:14:39,919
What seems to be the big problem here, little girl?

285
00:14:40,285 --> 00:14:42,052
How did you manage to get on this ship?

286
00:14:42,187 --> 00:14:43,012
Don't tell me.

287
00:14:43,037 --> 00:14:44,567
You're some kind of stowaway?

288
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,875
Do you know how we punish kids for doing that?

289
00:14:48,011 --> 00:14:49,845
We throw them straight into prison.

290
00:14:49,942 --> 00:14:51,242
Ten years minimum.

291
00:14:51,275 --> 00:14:53,686
And the worst part is, I'd be your warden!

292
00:14:53,775 --> 00:14:54,692
That what you want?

293
00:14:56,317 --> 00:14:57,275
No, 22!

294
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:58,841
Damn it! You're gonna pay!

295
00:14:58,930 --> 00:15:00,835
Hold it. I can handle this.

296
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:03,250
I got careless for a split second there.

297
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,955
But I've got this under control now, trust me.

298
00:15:06,161 --> 00:15:07,435
I gotta say.

299
00:15:07,609 --> 00:15:09,948
You sure do pack quite a powerful punch

300
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:11,414
for such a tiny girl.

301
00:15:11,817 --> 00:15:12,591
Now then.

302
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:14,044
This has been fun,

303
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:15,923
but it's time you started talk...

304
00:15:18,525 --> 00:15:19,442
Is he okay?

305
00:15:19,525 --> 00:15:20,650
Negative. He's dead.

306
00:15:20,713 --> 00:15:21,498
She's a monster!

307
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:24,261
The stowaway isn't gonna stop
until she gets the wooden cube!

308
00:15:24,359 --> 00:15:25,647
Let's charge at her together!

309
00:15:25,734 --> 00:15:26,787
We've got her outnumbered.

310
00:15:27,484 --> 00:15:28,702
Hmm.

311
00:15:28,817 --> 00:15:30,123
There's no reason to panic,

312
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:32,542
now that I'm here, so everybody can settle down.

313
00:15:32,567 --> 00:15:33,497
Officer!

314
00:15:37,774 --> 00:15:40,465
Relax. Just sit back and watch how it's done.

315
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,299
In this situation,

316
00:15:42,474 --> 00:15:44,902
the Officer might actually be our only hope.

317
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:49,043
Hmm. So, she's on a solo mission to claim the wooden cube.

318
00:15:49,109 --> 00:15:52,973
Undoubtedly a highly-skilled
agent sent by an unknown enemy.

319
00:15:53,125 --> 00:15:56,016
All that skill and power could be quite useful, though,

320
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:58,983
if we can convince her to switch over to our side.

321
00:15:59,248 --> 00:16:02,392
Fortunately, I am in possession of the other wooden cube.

322
00:16:02,417 --> 00:16:03,785
It's what she wants,

323
00:16:03,859 --> 00:16:05,574
so it makes the perfect bargaining chip,

324
00:16:05,812 --> 00:16:08,007
and we should be able to come to an agreement.

325
00:16:08,585 --> 00:16:11,184
I just happen to have the cube you're looking for,

326
00:16:11,275 --> 00:16:13,225
so what do you say we make a trade?

327
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,189
We could strike a promising deal...

328
00:16:15,359 --> 00:16:16,715
Ooh!

329
00:16:26,025 --> 00:16:26,961
Officer!

330
00:16:27,025 --> 00:16:28,054
He's dead, too!

331
00:16:28,214 --> 00:16:29,592
This is not good!

332
00:16:29,617 --> 00:16:31,806
She took down the Officer like it was nothing!

333
00:16:31,937 --> 00:16:32,804
We'll show you!

334
00:16:32,856 --> 00:16:34,923
We're not gonna let you out of here alive!

335
00:16:35,618 --> 00:16:38,266
This is bad! Really, really bad!

336
00:16:38,359 --> 00:16:41,515
By definition, that means it's not good.

337
00:16:43,575 --> 00:16:44,950
What does that mean, Scholar?

338
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,609
How bad is "really, really bad"?

339
00:16:46,986 --> 00:16:50,483
If you would all stop yelling at me for
a moment and observe the intruder's head,

340
00:16:50,525 --> 00:16:52,792
you'll notice that she has a wooden cube in her hair.

341
00:16:52,817 --> 00:16:56,094
And if you look on the other side of
her head, there's another wooden cube.

342
00:16:56,737 --> 00:16:58,976
Meaning that she has a total of two wooden cubes!

343
00:16:59,005 --> 00:17:01,547
Which means that she has both
wooden cubes in her possession!

344
00:17:02,092 --> 00:17:05,380
But even if she has both the cubes, we
should be fine as long as she doesn't know

345
00:17:05,414 --> 00:17:06,859
how to summon the ancient weapon.

346
00:17:06,922 --> 00:17:08,375
That's right! We can still win if...

347
00:17:08,427 --> 00:17:09,650
Shut up and listen to me!

348
00:17:10,085 --> 00:17:13,764
It says here in the Hell Encyclopedia,
that whoever possesses both of the wooden cubes

349
00:17:13,789 --> 00:17:16,662
will be bestowed with the
unstoppable power of the ancient weapon!

350
00:17:17,535 --> 00:17:18,588
In other words,

351
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:21,500
it means that whoever possesses both of the wooden cubes

352
00:17:21,525 --> 00:17:24,567
will be bestowed with the
unstoppable power of the ancient weapon.

353
00:17:24,603 --> 00:17:25,597
What does that mean?

354
00:17:25,622 --> 00:17:26,869
Explain that once more, please!

355
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,569
Yeah, I didn't get it the first time!

356
00:17:28,692 --> 00:17:29,542
In other...

357
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,877
There's no time to explain!

358
00:17:32,942 --> 00:17:33,910
It is over!

359
00:17:33,935 --> 00:17:36,078
If we try to fight here, not only will we be doomed,

360
00:17:36,103 --> 00:17:38,233
but the entire world along with us!

361
00:17:44,886 --> 00:17:46,823
Don't you dare back down!

362
00:17:48,075 --> 00:17:49,852
Never run from you fears!

363
00:17:49,942 --> 00:17:50,872
Conquer them!

364
00:17:53,286 --> 00:17:54,399
It's the Captain!

365
00:17:54,424 --> 00:17:55,366
Captain!

366
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:57,074
All right!

367
00:17:57,153 --> 00:18:01,782
Listen. Trying to attack her head-on one
at a time will only guarantee your demise.

368
00:18:01,953 --> 00:18:03,148
It would be futile.

369
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:06,114
However! The enemy is but one lone girl!

370
00:18:06,194 --> 00:18:08,424
So we have the advantage of numbers on our side!

371
00:18:08,498 --> 00:18:13,147
We must work together as a complete unit to rush in
and take those wooden cubes from her no matter the cost!

372
00:18:13,506 --> 00:18:15,464
I'll take point and lead the vanguard!

373
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:17,657
Attack!

374
00:18:20,427 --> 00:18:21,818
Captain!

375
00:18:22,317 --> 00:18:24,195
Forget about me! Carry on!

376
00:18:24,317 --> 00:18:25,419
But, we can't just...

377
00:18:25,528 --> 00:18:26,778
You piddling maggot!

378
00:18:26,862 --> 00:18:30,047
I don't remember training a
pathetic, cowardly soldier like you!

379
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:40,169
It's all over.

380
00:18:40,563 --> 00:18:41,947
The Officer is gone.

381
00:18:42,147 --> 00:18:43,887
The Captain is stuck in a hole.

382
00:18:44,432 --> 00:18:46,197
What hope do we have left now?

383
00:18:46,268 --> 00:18:47,097
We're a team.

384
00:18:47,122 --> 00:18:48,959
And we still have each other.

385
00:18:51,172 --> 00:18:54,946
One for all... and all for one!

386
00:19:13,211 --> 00:19:16,437
Captain, no!

387
00:19:17,478 --> 00:19:21,816
It's been 12 long years since I joined this squad.

388
00:19:23,243 --> 00:19:27,141
Over a decade of my life gone in a flash,

389
00:19:27,529 --> 00:19:30,387
because of this girl.

390
00:19:32,279 --> 00:19:33,764
It can't be over.

391
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,109
I'm not done yet.

392
00:19:37,839 --> 00:19:44,175
It won't end like this!

393
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:04,192
We're doomed!

394
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:05,174
Please, no!

395
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:06,857
I don't wanna die here!

396
00:20:30,059 --> 00:20:31,221
Huh?

397
00:20:34,426 --> 00:20:35,907
I'll go stand in the hallway.

398
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:45,010
Huh?

399
00:20:45,094 --> 00:20:46,317
That's so obvious!

400
00:20:46,938 --> 00:20:47,764
Whatever.

401
00:20:48,261 --> 00:20:51,875
I've got nothing else to do right now,
so I might as well indulge the little brat.

402
00:20:54,677 --> 00:20:57,010
Making something a waste of time

403
00:20:57,174 --> 00:20:59,233
is a special talent indeed.

404
00:21:07,442 --> 00:21:08,490
Hmm.

405
00:21:10,097 --> 00:21:11,377
Oh, you have bed-head.

406
00:21:11,402 --> 00:21:13,142
It's actually pretty cute on you.

407
00:21:14,768 --> 00:21:16,569
It looks pretty cute on you.

408
00:21:29,125 --> 00:21:30,613
What the hell am I doing?

409
00:21:30,647 --> 00:21:32,026
What's wrong with me?

410
00:21:36,359 --> 00:21:37,569
I'm finished now!

411
00:21:37,609 --> 00:21:39,586
The bath is all yours whenever you...

412
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:28,023
I'm a Love Umbrella.

413
00:23:28,131 --> 00:23:30,339
If you need a matchmaker, I've got you covered!

414
00:23:30,401 --> 00:23:33,589
Write your name on one side, and
your special someone on the other.

415
00:23:33,636 --> 00:23:34,862
Oh? You don't have one?

416
00:23:34,964 --> 00:23:39,160
Then for a sad sap like you, the
next <i>My Ordinary Life</i> is Episode 22.

417
00:23:39,185 --> 00:23:40,280
Look forward to it!

